import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Size')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of size?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['id'], data['size'], c=data['id'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('id')
    plt.ylabel('size')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between id and size?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="id")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    parent_counts = data['parent'].value_counts()
    parent_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    
    max_parent_value = parent_counts.idxmax()
    max_parent_count = parent_counts.max()
    
    plt.axhline(y=max_parent_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Most common parent: {max_parent_value} ({max_parent_count:.2f})')
    plt.xlabel('Parent Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common parent value?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(name_counts.index, name_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique values in the name field?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
